CSC 578 In-Class¶

Final Project¶

Project Objective:¶

Given a historical data of climate conditions from 2009 to 2016, predict the temperature of the next hour based on the climate conditions and temperature over the last 24 hours using Recurrent Neural Networks.

Correlation between features¶

Our target variable is T (degC). We can see that it has high correlation (|c|> 0.9) with Tpot(K), Tdew(degC), VPmax(mbar), and rho(g/m^3). It has very little correlation with p(mbar), wv(m/s), max.wv(m/s), wd(deg).

Training the Model¶

In [15]:
# 0 - single layer LSTM, GRU, or SimpleRNN
# 1 - stacking layers
# 2 - Bidirectional LSTMS
# 3 - CNN + RNN
NETWORK_TYPE = 0
In [16]:
bsize = 378                    # Size of training batches
single_units = 50              # Number of units for single layer network type
stacked_units1 = 100           # Number of units for first layer
stacked_units2 = 100           # Number of units for second layer
stacked_units3 = 50            # Number of units for third layer
bidir_units = 100              # Number of units for bidirectional layer
conv_units = 100               # Number of units for layer following convolutional layer
num_filters = 28               # Number of filters to use in convolutional layer
filter_size = 4                # Kernel size of filters
act_fcn = 'relu'               # activation function for convolution layer

if NETWORK_TYPE == 0:
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(LSTM(single_units, stateful = True,batch_input_shape=(bsize,train_x.shape[1], train_x.shape[2])))
    model.add(Dense(1))
    model.compile(loss='mae', optimizer='adam')
    # fit network
    history = model.fit(train_x, train_y, epochs=50, shuffle = False, batch_size = bsize)
    # plot history
    pyplot.plot(history.history['loss'], label='train')
    pyplot.legend()
    pyplot.show()
elif NETWORK_TYPE == 1:
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(LSTM(stacked_units1,return_sequences = True, input_shape=(train_x.shape[1], train_x.shape[2])))
    model.add(LSTM(stacked_units2,return_sequences = True))
    model.add(LSTM(stacked_units3))
    model.add(Dense(1))
    model.compile(loss='mae', optimizer='adam')
    # fit network
    history = model.fit(train_x, train_y, epochs=50, shuffle = False)
    # plot history
    pyplot.plot(history.history['loss'], label='train')
    pyplot.legend()
    pyplot.show()
elif NETWORK_TYPE == 2:
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(Bidirectional(LSTM(bidir_units,input_shape=(train_x.shape[1], train_x.shape[2]))))
    model.add(Dense(1))
    model.compile(loss='mae', optimizer='adam')
    # fit network
    history = model.fit(train_x, train_y, epochs=50, shuffle = False)
    # plot history
    pyplot.plot(history.history['loss'], label='train')
    pyplot.legend()
    pyplot.show()
elif NETWORK_TYPE == 3:
    # define CNN model
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(Conv1D(filters=num_filters, kernel_size=filter_size, activation=act_fcn, padding = 'same',input_shape=(train_x.shape[1], train_x.shape[2])))
    # define LSTM model
    model.add(LSTM(conv_units,return_sequences = True))
    model.add(Flatten())
    model.add(Dense(1))
    model.compile(loss='mae', optimizer='adam')
    # fit network
    history = model.fit(train_x, train_y, epochs=50, shuffle = False)
    # plot history
    pyplot.plot(history.history['loss'], label='train')
    pyplot.legend()
    pyplot.show()

Model Evaluation¶

If batch size is not implemented, model.predict will be run to make the predictions. If batch size is implemented, a model is created for the test set using the weights from the original model. Following this, the predictions are created.¶

In [19]:
#Evaluate Model
try:
    predictions = model.predict(test_x)
    predictions
except:
    # Evaluate Model when using Batch input shape
    # re-define model
    new_model = Sequential()
    new_model.add(LSTM(50, stateful = True,batch_input_shape=(1,train_x.shape[1], train_x.shape[2])))
    new_model.add(Dense(1))
    # copy weights
    old_weights = model.get_weights()
    new_model.set_weights(old_weights)
    # compile model
    new_model.compile(loss='mae', optimizer='adam')
    predictions = new_model.predict(test_x,batch_size = 1)

    for i in predictions_denorm:

        row.insert(0,sample['date time'][index])
        writer.writerow(row)
        index = index + 1
csvFile.close()
